Reviews: Came in today for an early dinner. First time here. Ordered the breaded fish fillet platter and the molcajete de Mariacos. The presentation of their dishes and drinks are appetizing and look really delicious, however, for my taste it was a bit lacking. This is just my opinion, the food needed to be better seasoned and needed salt. The fish in the molcajete was a bit fishy tasting and the shrimp needed some salt. Maybe it's an off day for them, who knows, will give them another try in the future.

Summary: There are mixed sentiments regarding the food quality at this Mexican restaurant. On the positive side, customers enjoyed the mariscos and found the food to be authentic Mexican cuisine. Some reviews praised the food quality as great, fresh, and hot. However, many reviews had negative comments regarding the food quality. Some reviews mentioned that the food was bland, off-tasting, or lacking seasoning. Others criticized specific dishes, such as a molcajete with fishy-tasting fish and shrimp that needed salt, or a burrito with no beans and small in size, and oily and unpleasant quesabirria. One review even mentioned burnt chicken and flavorless asada. Some mentioned that the food was not worth the price, and fajitas tasted like a microwaveable meal. A few reviews commented on oyster shots that were not good. There were also some reviews that described the food quality as mediocre, okay, or average. Overall, while there were some positive comments about the food quality, there were also many negative reviews.
